race.comment: Tricky race to kick off Geelong Cup Day. KARBURAN (6) is going well having given a sight up on speed when third at Moonee Valley last time out behind SUFFOLK STAR (10). SUFFOLK STAR was a long price that night, notching up his third win. Not much between the pair but it looks the right form and Kaburan can turn the tables. CABLE DANCER (3) should be ready to fire now third up to a staying trip. His best form reads well for this and he gets in relatively well considering that. NATURAL RULER (5) is on the up and gets to a staying trip for the first time in Australia which should see a better performance.
